The [http://commonsabundance.net Commons Abundance Network] (CAN) is a new project, to create an online social network for learning, collaboration and innovation to help build a commons-based economy of abundance.

A description of its vision and goals, and whom it may serve, are to be found on the [http://commonsabundance.net/home-page/about/ "About"] page.

[[NORA Commons Resource Model|NORA]] (Needs, Organizational form and Resources for Abundance) is the main page of a wiki, with the purpose of showing how commons organizational forms can allow us to use resources sustainably in order to meet needs to generate abundance. This is an important component of CAN.

CAN will help [[Coalescing around Abundance and the Commons|coalesce]] seemingly disparate initiatives toward a better world into a growing movement.

